            amount: "-",
            about: "The main goal of this project is to accurately determine the thermal-physical properties of 1-butanol in a wide range of temperatures and high pressures (up to 200 MPa) and, based on this data, to assess its application in technological processes. The main importance and relevance of the project is that 1-butanol is a promising substance as an alternative fuel and industrial solvent. The study of its behavior at high temperatures and pressures can lead to important applications in the energy, chemical, and petrochemical industries. Such studies are of great importance in the era of climate change and energy transition. In the project, experimental conditions were established to determine the thermal-physical parameters of 1-butanol, measurements were carried out at various pressure and temperature regimes, and the results were analyzed and compared with the existing literature. The project will be implemented by combining experimental and computational methods. High-precision devices will be used in laboratory conditions, and then the results will be analyzed with appropriate thermodynamic models. The main direction of the project is to present accurate thermophysical properties for 1-butanol in a wide range in tables and graphs, new proposals for assessing the suitability and improvement of existing models, and scientifically based recommendations for application areas. The results of the project can be applied in energy engineering, heat exchange systems, biofuel technologies, and the chemical industry. At the same time, the obtained data will be used in simulation programs and will contribute to more accurate modeling of real processes. This is expected to result in increasing the efficiency of technological processes and reducing energy losses.",
