            about: "The purpose of the project is to develop production processes for ferroalloys using local raw materials and organize the production of alloy steels at the country's metallurgical enterprises. The scientific idea of the project is to reveal complex physicochemical and metallurgical processes, thermodynamic parameters, and assess the role of ferroalloys in the deoxygenation and alloying of steel for the first time using local raw materials, and to establish a relationship between the production modes, structure, and properties of alloy steels obtained on the basis of this postulate. The expected development results of the project are to improve the quality of the deoxygenation process of steel using alloy steels and ferroalloys processed on the basis of local raw materials, and as a result, to obtain higher-quality electrical steel. It is precisely by increasing the quality of steel that its use for various structures will be possible. The scientific results obtained as a result of the research can allow the formation of new provisions based on innovative approaches in the field of metallurgy and materials science. The developed provisions can be used in metallurgical production and in the educational programs of relevant specialties. The scientific direction of the project is to conduct research on the organization of the production of ferroalloys using local raw materials. Ferroalloys are mainly used in the production of steel and cast iron. The quality of ferroalloys directly affects the quality of metallurgical products.",
